This will be the first episode in my training repo.
The purpose of this training will be to show the process of creating an ARM template in VS Code using IntelliSense and create a 1-click deploy button for GitHub for HTML.
#*Outline*#
Create GitHub Account

https://github.com/pricing

Install GitHub for desktop

https://desktop.github.com/

Install VS-Code

https://code.visualstudio.com/Download

Install Required Extensions for VS-Code

![alt text](https://github.com/christianhjohnson/TrainingRepo/blob/main/ARM%20Template%20Training/Pictures%20and%20Video%20for%20ARM%20Templates/github%20extensions.JPG)

Plan the resources to be deployed


Review configures for API-Version
Create the ARM templates with ARM extension
Create portion of ARM templates using intellisense
Create 1 click delpoyment button
